\noindent
\align left
\begin_inset Formula $\underline{H/N\ subgrupo}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left
Como 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 subgrupo de 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

, entonces 
\begin_inset Formula $1\in H\implies1N\in H/N$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left
Dados 
\begin_inset Formula $x,y\in H$
\end_inset

, tenemos que 
\begin_inset Formula $(xN)(yN)=(xy)N\in H/N,$
\end_inset

 pues 
\begin_inset Formula $xy\in H$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left
Dado 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in H$
\end_inset

, entonces 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{-1}\in H\implies x^{-1}N\in H/N$
\end_inset

.
 Y se tiene que 
\begin_inset Formula $xNx^{-1}N=xx^{-1}N=1=x^{-1}xN=x^{-1}NxN$
\end_inset

.
 Así, vemos que 
\begin_inset Formula $H/N$
\end_inset

 es subgrupo de 
\begin_inset Formula $G/N$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left

\bar under
Sea ahora 
\begin_inset Formula $K\ subgrupo\ de\ G/N$
\end_inset

 y sea 
\begin_inset Formula $J=\left\{ a\in G/aN\in K\right\} $
\end_inset


\bar default
, y definimos
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{ccccc}
G & \overset{f}{\rightarrow} & G/N & \overset{g}{\rightarrow} & \left(G/N\right)/K\\
a & \mapsto & aN\\
 &  & b & \mapsto & bK
\end{array}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left
Y sea 
\begin_inset Formula $h=g\circ f$
\end_inset

.
 Calculemos su núcleo:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
a\in Kerh\iff f(a)K=g(f(a))=1NK\iff f\left(a\right)=aN\in K\iff a\in J
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left
Es decir, 
\begin_inset Formula $Kerh=J\overset{lema\ 4.14.7}{\implies}J\ subgrupo\ de\ G$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left
Además, si 
\begin_inset Formula $a\in N\implies aN=1N\in K\implies a\in J$
\end_inset

.
 Es decir, 
\begin_inset Formula $N\subset J$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align left

\bar under
¿
\begin_inset Formula $J/N=K$
\end_inset

?
